│ This is an interesting bug in ScalarEvolution's exit value computation for PHI nodes. The  │
│ analysis incorrectly determined the exit value of `%indvar2`, leading `indvars` to perform │
│ an invalid constant-folding optimization.                                                  │
│                                                                                            │
│ The root cause is in `ScalarEvolution::computeSCEVAtScope`. When asked to compute the      │
│ value of a PHI node at the loop's exit scope, the logic for a loop with a known            │
│ backedge-taken count of zero was flawed. It was picking up the value from the backedge     │
│ instead of the preheader. A zero-trip loop never takes its backedge, so the PHI's value    │
│ upon exiting is the one from the incoming preheader block.                                 │
│                                                                                            │
│ The fix is to correct this logic. Instead of checking if an incoming block is *contained*  │
│ in the loop (`CurrLoop->contains(...)`), we should check if it's *not* contained in the    │
│ loop (`!CurrLoop->contains(...)`). This ensures we correctly select the value from the     │
│ preheader block for a zero-trip loop.                                                      │
│                                                                                            │
│ Here is the patch that implements this fix:                                                │
│                                                                                            │
│ ```diff                                                                                    │
│ --- a/llvm/lib/Analysis/ScalarEvolution.cpp                                                │
│ +++ b/llvm/lib/Analysis/ScalarEvolution.cpp                                                │
│ @@ -10087,13 +10087,13 @@                                                                  │
│            Value *InitValue = nullptr;                                                     │
│            bool MultipleInitValues = false;                                                │
│            for (unsigned i = 0; i < PN->getNumIncomingValues(); i++) {                     │
│ -            if (CurrLoop->contains(PN->getIncomingBlock(i))) {                            │
│ +            if (!CurrLoop->contains(PN->getIncomingBlock(i))) {                           │
│                if (!InitValue)                                                             │
│                  InitValue = PN->getIncomingValue(i);                                      │
│                else if (InitValue != PN->getIncomingValue(i)) {                            │
│                  MultipleInitValues = true;                                                │
│                  break;                                                                    │
│                }                                                                           │
│              }                                                                             │
│            }                                                                               │
│            if (!MultipleInitValues && InitValue)                                           │
│                                                                                            │
│ ```                                                                                        │
