│ This is a tricky bug in `ScalarEvolution`'s exit value computation. The core issue is that │
│ when `computeSCEVAtScope` is asked for the exit value of a PHI node (`%indvar2` in the     │
│ reproducer), it fails to correctly determine the value.                                    │
│                                                                                            │
│ The PHI node `%indvar2` is defined as `phi i32 [ 1, %entry ], [ %indvar3, %for.inc ]`.     │
│ When computing its value at the exit of the loop, we should consider the value coming from │
│ the backedge, which is `%indvar3`. However, `%indvar3` is itself a PHI node that is        │
│ variant within the loop.                                                                   │
│                                                                                            │
│ The existing logic in `computeSCEVAtScope` for `scUnknown` (which is how a PHI node is     │
│ represented) has a special case for when the backedge value is loop-invariant. This is not │
│ the case here. It then falls back to trying to constant-fold the PHI, but this also fails  │
│ because the value is not a simple constant.                                                │
│                                                                                            │
│ The correct approach is to recursively call `getSCEVAtScope` on the value from the         │
│ backedge. This allows `ScalarEvolution` to correctly trace the value of `%indvar3` to its  │
│ exit value, which is then used to compute the exit value of `%indvar2`.                    │
│                                                                                            │
│ The fix is to modify the logic that handles PHI nodes with a known backedge-taken count.   │
│ Instead of only handling loop-invariant backedge values, we should find the backedge       │
│ operand and compute its SCEV value at the loop's exit scope.                               │
│                                                                                            │
│ Here is the patch that implements this fix:                                                │
│                                                                                            │
│ ```diff                                                                                    │
│ --- a/llvm/lib/Analysis/ScalarEvolution.cpp                                                │
│ +++ b/llvm/lib/Analysis/ScalarEvolution.cpp                                                │
│ @@ -10102,11 +10102,13 @@                                                                  │
│          // for a loop which must execute the backedge?                                    │
│          if (!isa<SCEVCouldNotCompute>(BackedgeTakenCount) &&                              │
│              isKnownNonZero(BackedgeTakenCount) &&                                         │
│ -            PN->getNumIncomingValues() == 2) {                                            │
│ -                                                                                          │
│ -          unsigned InLoopPred =                                                           │
│ -              CurrLoop->contains(PN->getIncomingBlock(0)) ? 0 : 1;                        │
│ -          Value *BackedgeVal = PN->getIncomingValue(InLoopPred);                          │
│ -          if (CurrLoop->isLoopInvariant(BackedgeVal))                                     │
│ -            return getSCEV(BackedgeVal);                                                  │
│ +            PN->getNumIncomingValues() > 1) {                                             │
│ +          for (unsigned i = 0, e = PN->getNumIncomingValues(); i != e; ++i) {             │
│ +            if (CurrLoop->contains(PN->getIncomingBlock(i))) {                            │
│ +              // This is the backedge.                                                    │
│ +              return getSCEVAtScope(PN->getIncomingValue(i), L);                          │
│ +            }                                                                             │
│ +          }                                                                               │
│          }                                                                                 │
│          if (auto *BTCC = dyn_cast<SCEVConstant>(BackedgeTakenCount)) {                    │
│            // Okay, we know how many times the containing loop executes.  If               │
│                                                                                            │
│ ```                                                                                        │
