│ This is a subtle bug in `ScalarEvolution`'s computation of loop exit values for PHI nodes. │
│ The miscompilation occurs because `indvars` relies on `ScalarEvolution` to determine the   │
│ value of `%indvar2` at the loop's exit. `ScalarEvolution` provides an incorrect value,     │
│ leading to an invalid constant-folding optimization.                                       │
│                                                                                            │
│ The problematic PHI is `%indvar2 = phi i32 [ 1, %entry ], [ %indvar3, %for.inc ]`. Its     │
│ value at the loop exit depends on the exit value of `%indvar3`. The logic in               │
│ `computeSCEVAtScope` for `SCEVUnknown` (which represents the PHI) needs to handle this     │
│ dependency correctly.                                                                      │
│                                                                                            │
│ When computing the exit value of a PHI, we are interested in the value it takes from the   │
│ backedge on the final iteration. The existing logic had a check for a loop-invariant       │
│ backedge value, but in this case, the backedge value (`%indvar3`) is itself loop-variant.  │
│                                                                                            │
│ The correct fix is to find the incoming value from the backedge and recursively call       │
│ `getSCEVAtScope` on it. This allows `ScalarEvolution` to correctly determine the exit      │
│ value of `%indvar3` and then use that to compute the exit value of `%indvar2`.             │
│                                                                                            │
│ The original code had a special case for PHIs with exactly two incoming values. This is    │
│ too restrictive. The fix is to generalize this to any PHI, find the backedge operand, and  │
│ recursively compute its value at the loop's exit scope.                                    │
│                                                                                            │
